attributes.Long form description: The student takes the wheels off the base frame, then the upper tray, then the tray in the middle, then the bottom tray. The student takes the upper side bars off, then the bars on the lower side. The student finishes by taking the base frame apart.

attributes.Transcription: You can now disassemble the Rashult rolling shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the wheels from the base frame.
The student disassembles the upper tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts the wrench by the wrong side, so the angle formed does not allow either loosen or tighten.
The student accidentally drops the bracket.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the tray in the middle.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student inserts the wrench by the wrong side, so the angle formed does not allow either loosen or tighten.
The student rotates the wrench in the tightening direction, but he wants to disassemble, therefore he has to loosen.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the bottom tray.
The student disassembles the upper side bars.
The student disassembles the bars on the lower side.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student accidentally drops the third screw.

attributes.Transcription: You can now stop the recording.
